There are 4 types of Programming languages paradigms that you need to know:
1. *Procedural* An example would be C. A simple procedure is defined and everything is defined sequentially!
2. *Object Oriented* Code is modelled in terms of real-life objects
For example take the example of a College!
A college has data types like number of students, professors, etc.
I'll talk about this in sometime!
3. Functional Programming : These are modelled in terms of mathematical functions! You can ask the guys in the Erlang SUmmer Project about them!

>Inheritance can be defined as the process where one class acquires the 
properties (methods and fields) of another. With the use of inheritance 
the information is made manageable in a hierarchical order.
>-Tutorials Point
Basically the idea is assume there are two classes: *Parent* and *Child*
Now the Child will have the characteristics of the parent and some of its own!
The characteristics of the parent are said to be *inherited*
So let's say if I have a method called isMale() defined in a parent class, the same method does not need to be defined again in the child class!
